As every class extends the object class. THe collection framework is also there which is the collection of many data structure. they also extends it.

But one thing is there, the primitives never uses / extends the classes.
They directly store the values

So java has made Classes for primitive datatypes those classes are called as Wrapper Class.
int -> Integer, char -> Character , double -> Double
Kabhi kabhi hi inka kaam padta hai


int num = 1;
Integer num1 = num;
System.out.println(num1);

Here we assigned Primitive to the ref var of Integer.
This is Clas Autoboxing
(Primitive se obj me bnaa daale)

Vice versa bhi hota hai jbb

int num2 = num1.intValue();
System.out.println(num2);

This is clas AutoUnBoxing
===============================
String -> int

String s = "12"
int num = Integer.parseInt(s) -> by using parseInt function any string will be converted into Int